kerchunk (1.0.1-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fix COR polarity: CM108 inverts internally, default now active_high
  * Fix COR HID read: drain all queued reports, use last state
  * Fix PTT pin: GPIO2 for CM108 RIM-Lite (was wrong pin)
  * Fix module install path: /usr/lib/kerchunk (was multiarch path)
  * Fix socket path: /run/kerchunk/kerchunk.sock
  * Fix audio jitter: pad partial queue drain frames with silence
  * Fix resampler underrun: ramp down instead of hard zero (clicks)
  * Add kerchunk-diag: standalone PTT/audio/COR diagnostic tool
  * Add HID debug logging for COR troubleshooting
  * Use /dev/rimlite udev symlink as default HID device
  * Update README with RIM-Lite GPIO mapping and polarity notes

 -- Brian West <brian@mcalester.net>  Sun, 29 Mar 2026 20:00:00 -0500

kerchunk (1.0.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian package release
  * kerchunkd GMRS/HAM repeater controller daemon
  * kerchunk CLI for runtime control
  * 24 dynamically loaded modules
  * Embedded HTTPS web dashboard with WebSocket audio
  * FCC 95.1751 compliant CW ID and voice identification
  * NWS alert monitoring with TTS announcements
  * Systemd service with security hardening

 -- Brian West <brian@mcalester.net>  Fri, 27 Mar 2026 12:00:00 -0500
